Title: Object: Cleopatra, Queen of Egypt
Description: Head and shoulders directed to right, head in profile, wearing a rich low-necked gown with ruffs at her shoulders, a jewelled necklace, diadem, earrings and ropes of pearl and a veil in her hair which is dressed up in classical style; oval format with a plaque showing her receiving Anthony below; one of a series. 1804 Colour stipple and etching
Curator's comments: One of a number of stipple heads of Kings and Queens of similar format printed on quarto sheets, by Chapman, published by J. Wilkes, 1795-1810 (1943,1113.205-210, 212-239, 242-246). They probably appeared as illustrations to the 'Encyclopaedia Londinensis, Universal Dictionary of Arts, Sciences and Literature ... Embellished by ... engravings. Compiled ... by John Wilkes' (24 volumes, published 1810-1829, primarily by J. Wilkes, some volumes by G Jones).
